overview: The user initiated a project to build a Sleep Questionnaire
  Application, focusing on database integration, a client dashboard, and
  authentication. The agent evaluated the existing codebase, identified missing
  components, and developed a comprehensive plan. Key decisions included using
  NeonDB for PostgreSQL, implementing a QuestionnaireResponse model, and
  creating API endpoints for data management. A significant pivot occurred when
  the user inquired about authentication complexity, leading to a simplified
  solution leveraging Next.js middleware for route protection and a basic
  cookie-based session. The agent guided the user through database setup and
  environment variable configuration. Initial browser testing confirmed the
  authentication and API routes were functional, but a full end-to-end test of
  questionnaire submission to the database is still in progress.
